description:
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a resourceful and enthusiastic person with initiative to join the clerical team in the Radiology Department at the Royal Bournemouth Hospital. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Primarily the job role involves the making of X-Ray, Ultrasound and Medical Physics appointments over the telephone, by letter and also face to face with the patient.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;There will also be other clerical tasks to perform such as covering reception and general administrative office duties as required.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This is a busy, varied and demanding post in a progressive department, where we aim to deliver high quality care to all our patients.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Hours of work: 37.5 hours per week to be worked flexibly between 7:45am and 5.30pm, Monday to Friday.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is anticipated that the Royal Bournemouth and Christchurch Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust and Poole Hospital NHS Foundation Trust will merge in 2020 to University Hospitals Dorset NHS Foundation Trust. It is a condition of employment that all staff being recruited in the period before merger will work across all sites pre and post-merger&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview Date: to be confirmed&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Francesca Endicott - Radiology Administration Manager Email address: francesca.endicott@rbch.nhs.uk Telephone number 0300 019 6250&lt;/p&gt;
